docs.abstract: The layoffs will focus on human resources and its retail division, Amazon’s chief executive said in an email to employees.
docs.snippet: The layoffs will focus on human resources and its retail division, Amazon’s chief executive said in an email to employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon plans to eliminate 18,000 corporate and technology jobs in a significant expansion of its cost-cutting plans, the company’s chief executive, Andy Jassy, said in a message to employees on Wednesday.

headline.main: Amazon Expands Corporate Layoffs to 18,000 Jobs
headline.print_headline: As Growth Slows, Amazon Announces It Will Expand Layoffs

docs.abstract: To land the House speaker position, the California Republican will have to win over opponents who question his ties to Silicon Valley and his commitment to right wing causes.
docs.snippet: To land the House speaker position, the California Republican will have to win over opponents who question his ties to Silicon Valley and his commitment to right wing causes.
docs.lead_paragraph: Representative Kevin McCarthy, Republican of California, is still working on landing the House speaker gig after six failed attempts. It’s the first such House floor showdown in a century, and business is at the heart of his woes.

headline.main: Kevin McCarthy’s Business Ties Complicate His Rise to Power

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: The company’s grip on ticket sales, and its move last year to cancel sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming tour, will be a big focus of an antitrust-focused hearing.
docs.snippet: The company’s grip on ticket sales, and its move last year to cancel sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming tour, will be a big focus of an antitrust-focused hearing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two months after Ticketmaster canceled sales for Taylor Swift’s upcoming Eras tour, a top executive from its parent company, Live Nation Entertainment, will appear at the Senate on Tuesday to defend the company. (Ms. Swift herself is not scheduled to show up.)

headline.main: Live Nation Faces a Skeptical Senate

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: Elliott Management, the $55 billion hedge fund, has taken a big stake in the struggling tech giant, putting more pressure on its co-founder, Marc Benioff.
docs.snippet: Elliott Management, the $55 billion hedge fund, has taken a big stake in the struggling tech giant, putting more pressure on its co-founder, Marc Benioff.
docs.lead_paragraph: Salesforce has been through a lot of turbulence lately, including a huge round of layoffs and a shake-up in its top ranks. Now it faces a big new threat in Elliott Management, the $55 billion hedge fund that has taken a significant stake in the company.

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: The software company plans to cut around 8,000 jobs as business slows for tech companies. “We hired too many people leading into this economic downturn,” Salesforce’s chief executive said.
docs.snippet: The software company plans to cut around 8,000 jobs as business slows for tech companies. “We hired too many people leading into this economic downturn,” Salesforce’s chief executive said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Salesforce, the business software giant, said on Wednesday that it planned to lay off 10 percent of its work force, or about 8,000 employees, and scale back office space because of concerns about the economy.

headline.main: Salesforce to Lay Off 10% of Staff and Cut Office Space
headline.print_headline: Salesforce to Lay Off 10% of Staff and Cut Office Space

byline.original: By Isabella Simonetti and Kalley Huang

docs.abstract: Hindenburg Research accused the Adani Group of orchestrating the “largest con in corporate history,”  sending shares of its companies tumbling on Wednesday.
docs.snippet: Hindenburg Research accused the Adani Group of orchestrating the “largest con in corporate history,”  sending shares of its companies tumbling on Wednesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Hindenburg Research, the short seller that rose to prominence by going after unprofitable blank-check firms and crypto companies, is pursuing its biggest targets yet: the Indian conglomerate Adani Group and its billionaire founder, Gautam Adani, whom Forbes ranks as the world’s third-richest person.

headline.main: A Short Seller Takes Aim at an Indian Corporate Giant
